27 Sep 2025
Chris Bouchard

* python script implementing the replica trick with quenched lattice QCD gauge fields
* built fropm qLQCD-generate, implemented by Lukas Wystemp (U of Manchester) in summer 2025
  - uses ReplicaLattice class 
  - user interface via Replica_generate_multiprocessing.py
  - implemented for Wilson action (W=Wilson) without tadpole improvement
* helper functions and classes in gauge_latticeqcd.py and lattice_collection.py
  includes code to update the lattices and perform measurements.
* calculation of lattice spacing from beta follows Necco and Sommer, NPB 622, 328-346 
  (2002), hep-lat/0108008
* list of files and description:
  . Replica_generate_multiprocessing.py: user interface  
  . params.py: values of needed constants
  . tools_v1.py: contains some useful functions
  . gauge_latticeqcd.py: where code does the majority of the work generating a Markov chain
  . lattice_collection.py: contains useful functions
  . replicate_generate.py: user interface without multiprocessing
  . action_v_cfg.py: for analysing thermalisation of lattices
  . plaq_v_cfg.py: for analysing thermalisation of lattices
  . replica_analysis.py: preliminary analysis of replica lattices
  . replica_analysis_2.py: preliminary analysis of replica lattices
* 27 Sep 2025, ver 2.0
  . fixed calculation of staples in gauge_latticeqcd.py to account for opposite orientation



